    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION, TANDEM AXLE: INTERNATIONAL - DISASSEMBLE - DIFFERENTIAL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1400905" svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>DIFFERENTIAL</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400914">Figure 14</hotlnk>
            </title>
            <figure id="f1400914" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400914" filename="../figg14/g1400914.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Differential Components</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. ADJUSTING RING</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. LOCK</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. BEARING CUP</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. BEARING CONE</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. FLANGE HALF DIFFERENTIAL CASE</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. RING GEAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. RIVET</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. DIFFERENTIAL SIDE GEAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. THRUST WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>13. THRUST WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>14. DIFFERENTIAL CASE HALF</callout1>
                    <callout1>15. BEARING CONE</callout1>
                    <callout1>16. BEARING CUP</callout1>
                    <callout1>17. DIFFERENTIAL BEARING CAP BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>18. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>19. LOCK</callout1>
                    <callout1>20. BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>21. ADJUSTING RING</callout1>
                    <callout1>22. DIFFERENTIAL SIDE BEARING CAP</callout1>
                    <callout1>23. DIFFERENTIAL CASE BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>24. DIFFERENTIAL CROSS SHAFT</callout1>
                    <callout1>25. DIFFERENTIAL PINION MATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>26. THRUST WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>27. DIFFERENTIAL SIDE BEARING CAP</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Match mark differential case halves with punch or chisel for correct alignment in
                    reassembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400915">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400915" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400915" filename="../figg14/g1400915.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 15. Match Mark Differential Case Halves</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove differential case bolts and lift off the differential case half.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove thrust washer and differential side gear.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift out cross shaft, pinion mates and thrust washers.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove second differential side gear and thrust washer.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If differential side bearings are to be replaced, remove old bearings using suitable
                    puller (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400916">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400916" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400916" filename="../figg14/g1400916.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 16. Remove Old Bearings</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Inspect all parts, including the machined surfaces of case itself.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>If any gears are to be replaced, they must be replaced in sets. Inspect thrust washers for
                            scoring and excessive wear. Replace all worn or damaged parts.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When it is necessary to remove ring gear from differential case, carefully center punch
                    each rivet head. Use a 9/16" drill bit and drill through rivet heads (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400917">Figure 17</hotlnk>). Next, use a rounded type punch to drive out the
                    remaining portion of the rivet.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400917" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400917" filename="../figg14/g1400917.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 17. Drill Through Rivet Heads</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Always use a soft metal hammer or H.D. plastic head hammer to strike punch.</para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>Wear safe eye protection. Do not hit steel parts with a steel hammer. Parts can break and
                            cause injury.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Do not use a chisel to remove rivet heads, as damage to differential case may result.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
